---
title: Bottle Gourd Raita
servings: 2
---

>> A simple and comforting South Indian-style raita with bottle gourd, curd, and South Indian tempering.

== Ingredients ==
@bottle gourd{1 small}
@curd{1 cup}
@salt{to taste}

== Tempering ==
@oil{1 tsp}
@mustard seeds{1 tsp}
@cumin seeds{1 tsp}
@dried red chillies{1-2}
@curry leaves{a few}

== Optional Additions ==
@coriander leaves{}
@green chilli{1}

== Method ==

Heat @oil{1 tsp} in a #pan.

Add @mustard seeds{1 tsp} and let them splutter.

Add @cumin seeds{1 tsp}, @dried red chillies{1-2}, and @curry leaves{a few}.

Add finely chopped @bottle gourd{1 small} and sauté until soft and cooked.

Let the bottle gourd cool slightly.

Mix it with @curd{1 cup} in a #bowl.

Add @salt{to taste} and mix well.

Serve chilled or at room temperature.
